{
  "texts": [
    "Recent research has raised questions, such as \"Should tools always be used?\"",
    "More specifically, whether the performance improvements brought by using tools justify the extra computational costs incurred during model training or the inference costs during testing.",
    "Existing work mainly focuses on task accuracy, but studying the cost-effectiveness of these methods is also a valuable topic.",
    "6.2.2 Real-time Properties of GenIR Systems.",
    "Timeliness is critical for GenIR systems, as well as traditional IR systems, to provide users with the most up-to-date information."
  ]
}